<Window x:Class="WPF_BlackJack.Presentation.BlackJackRules"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:WPF_BlackJack.Presentation"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="BlackJackRules" Height="550" Width="800" WindowStartupLocation="CenterScreen">
    <Grid>
        <Grid Background="DarkSlateGray">
            <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
                <ColumnDefinition Width="*"/>
            </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <Grid.RowDefinitions>
                <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="5*"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            </Grid.RowDefinitions>

            <Label Content="BlackJack Rules" HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" FontSize="36" Foreground="LightGreen"/>

            <TextBlock Grid.Column="0" Grid.Row="1" FontSize="17" Padding="5" Foreground="White">
                Below you will find the definition of common terms and the rules to play BlackJack.
                <LineBreak/>
                <LineBreak/>
                <Bold Foreground="LightGreen">Hit</Bold> = Have the dealer deal you a new card.
                <LineBreak/>
                <Bold Foreground="LightGreen">Stand</Bold> = Stop having cards dealt to you, and stay with your current total
                <LineBreak/>
                <Bold Foreground="LightGreen">Bust</Bold> = You have exceeded 21 and have busted (Loss)
                <LineBreak/>
                <LineBreak/>
                <Bold Foreground="LightGreen">Objective:</Bold>
                <LineBreak/>
                The Objective of BlackJack is to reach a card total of 21. You are dealt 2 cards initially. The face value
                <LineBreak/>
                of the cards is what the total is. Ace can be either a 1 or 11 depending on what you need. All royal cards
                <LineBreak/>
                Are a value of 10. The dealer will be dealt one card face up, and one card face down. The dealer must
                <LineBreak/>
                stand on all values over 17 and hit on all values 16 and under. Whoever has the highest total
                <LineBreak/>
                at the end wins the round and the bet.
            </TextBlock>

            <Button Grid.Column="0" Grid.Row="2" Width="100" Height="50" Content="Close" FontSize="30" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Margin="10" Click="Button_Click">
                
            </Button>

        </Grid>
    </Grid>
</Window>
